The Bank of England said it provided themoney market with a further 20 mln stg of assistance during themorning. It again bought bills for resale to the market onApril 2 at a rate of 10-15/16 pct. Earlier this morning, itbought 17 mln stg of bills at the same rate and for resale onthe same date.    The Bank has thus given a total of 37 mln stg so far today,which leaves the bulk of a 1.15 billion stg shortage still inthe system. Dealers noted that money market rates again easedthis morning and the Bank may have refused bill offers from thediscount houses at rates below its established dealing levels. REUTER&#3;